#README

##MVAPICH with IB

To install the necessary files for a new cloudlab instance.
1. Get a Cloudlab instance:
    - Get profile IBMellanox:8 (Project LSM) or get the profile from https://pastebin.com/p4C8pWYt
2. $ bash <(wget --no-check-certificate -qO- https://www.ilab.cs.rutgers.edu/~ssg128/naastik/hpcsetup.sh)
3. $ cd ssd/Crosslayer
4. $ source scripts/setvars.sh
5. $ source scripts/setalias.sh
6. $ kernel compile
7. $ sudo reboot
8. $ sudo mount /dev/sda4 ssd
9. Repeat steps 3, 4, 5 - sudo sysctl -w kernel.perf_event_paranoid=0; sudo sysctl -w kernel.kptr_restrict=0
10. $ install_mvapich.sh
11. $ vtune-install
12. For multi-user support, all this has to be done on other nodes also.
